Package game

Class Level

java.lang.Object
game.Level
public class Level extends Object
Level is the class that contains the information for each level of Geometry Dash.
Author:
Caleb Chang, Justin Chai

  • Constructor Details

    • Level

      public Level(Point[] obstacleCoordsBlueprint, Point[] platCoordsBlueprint)
      Constructor for Level. Initializes the obstacles, platforms, player, ground, obstacle coordinates, and platform coordinates. The #move() method for player is overwritten using an anonymous class to provide functionality for jumping.
      Parameters:
      obstacleCoordsBlueprint - The shape of the obstacles.
      platCoordsBlueprint - The shape of the platforms.

    • paintLevel

      public void paintLevel(Graphics brush)
      Contains all the logic for interactions between the elements.

      If the game is not over, all the elements are painted with the brush parameter. Otherwise, display the appropriate end screen depending on if the level was passed or not. If the player collides with the ground or with the top of any platform, it is able to jump. If the player collides with any obstacles or any other side of a platform, the game ends. If all obstacles and platforms are no longer on the screen, the level is complete.

      Parameters:
      brush -

    • elementsOnScreen

      private boolean elementsOnScreen()
      Checks to see if there are any more obstacles or platforms on the screen. Used by paintLevel(Graphics) when checking if the level is complete.
      Returns:
      True if there are elements still on screen. False otherwise.
      See Also:
